angeable with   Rickman  , especially in recent times.","English: occasionally perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>riche</i> ‘rich, powerful’ + <i>-man</i>. Compare   Rich  .","English: perhaps a variant of   Richmond  , or vice versa."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":17,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":26,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":61,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Richmond was born in Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England. He married Mrs. Thomas Richmond before 1316, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1316."},"et":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"enne 1316","England":"England","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"ennen vuotta 1316","England":"England","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"avant 1316","England":"Angleterre","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Richmond est né à Burton Constable, Everwyck, Angleterre. Il a épousé Mrs. Thomas Richmond avant 1316, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1316."},"de":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"vor 1316","England":"England","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Richmond wurde in Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England geboren. Er hat vor 1316 in England Mrs. Thomas Richmond geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1316."},"ht":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"Desede","–Male":"Desede","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"before 1316","England":"England","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England"},"hu":{"–1316":"–1316","–Female":"elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","before 1316":"1316 előtt","England":"England","Burton Constable, Yorkshire, England":"Burton Constable